events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton scored 24 points and Giannis Antetokounmpo had his first triple-double of the season to lead the Milwaukee Bucks to a 112-97 victory over the short-handed New York Knicks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Balanced Bucks cruise past short-handed Knicks 112-97

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored an NBA season-high 51 points in the Brooklyn Nets' 116-104 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant scores 51 in Nets' 116-104 win over slumping Pistons

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson had 18 points and nine rebounds while starting in place of injured star Luka Doncic, leading the Dallas Mavericks to a 103-84 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavericks, minus Doncic, beat Thunder 103-84 behind Brunson

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Jakob Poeltl had 24 points and 12 rebounds, Derrick White added 24 points, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the New Orleans Pelicans 112-97 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Poeltl's double-double helps Spurs defeat Pelicans, 112-97

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 23 points and 10 rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves snapped a five-game losing streak with a 116-111 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves snap losing streak with 116-111 win in Portland

events.name: Orlando Magic at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James finished playing back-to-back road games in the Midwest on Friday, flew to Phoenix on Saturday to watch his son play, and then dropped a triple-double on the Orlando Magic back in LA on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 30, Lakers top Magic 106-94 for 5th win in 7
